-- BAT Uganda Says It Plans to Plant 2.5 Million Trees for Curing
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2012-03-23T07:21:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-23/bat-uganda-says-it-plans-to-plant-2-5-million-trees-for-curing.html
British American Tobacco Uganda Ltd. (BATU) 
plans to plant 2.5 million trees this year as it strives to
become self-reliant in the wood it needs for curing the crop.  BAT  Uganda  has raised 2.3 million eucalyptus seedlings and
will also plant indigenous varieties, the Kampala-based company
said in an advert published today in New Vision newspaper. BAT
said it started a tree-planting program in 2004 with the aim of
being self-reliant by 2015.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  